<item>
            <title>[LU-4739] Code inconsistencies when referring to config_llog_instance</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4739</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While trying to search for other similar occurrences of an issue I was working to keep consistent with current coding conventions I found that there are two instances where the local variable pointer name of the config_llog_instance was inconsistent with the way it is done in other areas of the code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most of the files do the following:&lt;br/&gt;
struct config_llog_instance *cfg&lt;br/&gt;
or &lt;br/&gt;
struct config_llog_instance lcfg&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;obd_config.c and obd_mount_server.c both have functions that use the following method:&lt;br/&gt;
struct config_llog_instance *clli&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
